</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>69
 See, for example, Salvia and others,<i> Desajustes en el desarrollo </i>(see footnote 51), pp. 51-60, 
</p>
<p>estimating that in December 2012 between 24.5 and 26.9 per cent of the population in urban regions 
lived below the poverty line and that between 4.9 and 5.8 per cent faced extreme poverty. Similar 
results have been reported in CIPPES, <i>Pobreza e Indigencia en Argentina 2013</i>, Diciembre 2013, 
available from www.cippes.org/cippes-uploads/archivos/boletin_pobreza_jun_2013_cippes.pdf. 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>70
 The official poverty line is measured by INDEC based on a basket of basic goods, food and services, 
</p>
<p>while the extreme poverty line (<i>indigencia</i>) is based on a food basket containing only products 
representing minimum dietary needs. </p>

